  Kit-version guards

  - The dropdown handler uses getattr(self, "_movie_capture_controller", None) and

  hasattr(controller, "apply_live_preset") so older controller instances that pre-date this

  change don't crash the UI.

  - _BUILTIN_RENDER_MODE lookup before applying — unknown preset keys log + skip rather than

  raise.

  - All new carb.settings calls run through the existing RenderPresetManager apply/restore

  plumbing, which already swallows per-key set/get failures so a missing key on a different

  Kit build degrades gracefully.

  Path-traced capture interaction

  Verified the capture-time backend (extension.py:821, 898–899) saves

  /rtx/pathtracing/spp/totalSpp on start and restores them on finish — restoring to the

  live-applied values. So: live preview → start capture → finish → live preview is still

  applied. The capture's restore does not clobber the live token.
